Installed 

NOdejs, YeoMan , Gulp and Bower 
https://blog.teamtreehouse.com/improving-development-workflow-yeoman
https://blog.teamtreehouse.com/getting-started-with-grunt
http://yeoman.io/learning/

http://www.dappuniversity.com/articles/web3-js-intro

Not using Grunt as of now .. will explore later 

> npm install -g yo@latest

Install a webapp generator from a various options available I have used webapp generator

> npm install -g generator-webapp

Generate the project skeleton using 
> yo webapp

Bower is used to install further dependencies like Web3 
> bower install web3

to run local server use
> gulp serve

> For the sample application use the geth node running to with JSON RPC options "web3, eth, net, personal"
> we can use TestRPC (Ganache) but account Locking and Unlocking might not support 
> MetaMask also does not support all API's do have a check 



